FINAL CURSOR RULES — 2025 Edition (Next.js, RSC, TS, Tailwind)
 Core TypeScript & Code Quality

No unused imports, variables, parameters, or dead code.
Use arrow functions for all components & helpers.
Explicit argument + return types for all helpers.
Only TypeScript code — no JS files.
Do NOT use React.FC.
Component signature: (props: Props): JSX.Element.
TypeScript strict mode required:
strict: true
noImplicitAny: true
strictNullChecks: true
Avoid any. Use unknown and cast properly.
No barrel imports (no index.ts re-exports).
No inline styles & no logic inside JSX.
Use Tailwind for styling.
Naming conventions:
Components → PascalCase
Functions/variables → camelCase
Constants → UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
No console logs in production.
Only console.error allowed with justification comment.
 Do NOT use useMemo, useCallback, or memo unless absolutely required.
 Folder Structure & Organization

src/
  constants/
  helpers/
  types/
  store/
    <slice-name>/
      index.ts
      constants.ts
      helpers.ts
      api.ts
  hooks/
  providers/
  components/
    shared/
  features/
  services/ or api/
  styles/
  tests/
Component Folder Structure

components/<ComponentName>/
  index.tsx
  constants.ts
  helpers.ts
  types.ts
Small single-use components → 1 file.
Shared reusable UI → components/shared/.
Use error boundaries for runtime safety.
 State Management (Zustand/Redux) — RSC Optimized

 CRITICAL RULES

 Never store server-fetched data in Zustand or Redux.
 Never hydrate server data into client stores.
Zustand is ONLY for client-side UI logic:
modals
filters (client only)
toggles
forms
ephemeral UI state
Store Rules
Each slice must contain:

index.ts
constants.ts
helpers.ts
api.ts
Request Status Enum
src/types/request-status.ts

export enum RequestStatus {
  Init = 'init',
  Pending = 'pending',
  Fulfilled = 'fulfilled',
  Rejected = 'rejected',
}
Slice Access Rule (NEW)

Do NOT access entire Zustand store.
Always access only the specific key:
const value = useStore((state) => state.someKey);
 Next.js Best Practices (App Router + RSC)

Use <Image> for images; <Script> for scripts.
Metadata goes in layout (title, description, OG, Twitter).
Add organization schema (JSON-LD).
Header & Footer rendered only in layout.
Preload critical assets (preload, preconnect).
Preload LCP image with priority.
Use .webp images by default.
Add correct CDN caching headers.
Add sitemap.xml, robots.txt, llms.txt.
Avoid use client unless required.
No client fetching for initial render.
Dynamic data must be fetched via:
Server Components
use server functions
use cache
 Server Data Architecture & use cache Rules
A. Server Components Fetch Their Own Data

All backend calls occur inside Server Components.
No API calls in Client Components.
B. All server utilities must use:

'use server';
C. Use use cache for shared/frequent server data

'use server';
import { use cache } from 'react';

export const getUserProfile = use cache(async (id: string) => {
  const res = await fetch(`${process.env.API_URL}/users/${id}`);
  return res.json();
});
Rules:

Must be defined outside components.
Must be used when multiple components fetch the same data.
Do NOT wrap browser APIs.
Only for server-cacheable async logic.
D. No Prop Drilling of Server Data

If multiple components need the same data → use cached server function.
Pass to client components only when required.
E. NEVER sync server data → Zustand

No server → client-store hydration.
No store-based server data reading.
 Page & Feature Structure

Pages import + render a single root feature component.
Folder structure must mirror the page UI:
features/<page>/
  index.tsx
  components/
  helpers.ts
  constants.ts
  types.ts
Fetch all server data at page/layout level.
Reuse it with use cache.
Components < 200 lines (unless justified).
Child components must be split logically.
Lists → dedicated item components, unique keys.
Only Tailwind for styling.
Add data-testid for important elements.
 Styling & Theming

Tailwind CSS only.
No inline styles or custom <style> tags.
Use semantic design tokens.
Avoid !important.
Classnames must be readable and composable.
 Images & Performance

Use .webp format.
Above-the-fold images must have priority.
Use Next.js responsive image features.
Preload fonts + critical files.
Ensure CDN caching headers.
 Code Splitting & Performance

Use next/dynamic for heavy/interaction-only components:
with skeleton fallback
with ssr: false when needed
Lazy load all non-critical UI.
Prefer SSG/ISR when possible.
Reduce re-renders through good component boundaries.
Use use cache for expensive repeated server operations.
 Do NOT use useMemo, useCallback, or memo unless absolutely necessary because RSC + React Compiler optimizes automatically.
 Final Summary

All data fetching happens in Server Components.
Use use server for server functions.
Use use cache for repeated/expensive server calls.
Zustand is UI-only, never stores server data.
Strict TypeScript + Tailwind only.
Clean folder structure.
No memo/useMemo/useCallback.
Always select slice keys instead of entire Zustand store.
